==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fleshpot
<hw>Flesh"pot`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A pot
or vessel in which flesh is cooked.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In the land of Egypt . . . we sat by the <qex>fleshpots</qex>, and
. . . did eat bread to the full.</q> <rj><qau>Ex. xvi. 3.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>hence</specif>, <pluf>pl.</pluf> <def>plenty;
high living.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <pluf>pl.</pluf> <def>Places providing opportunity to
indulge in amusements or pleasures without moral restraints.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fleshquake</ent>⟦br⟧
